957
00:52:49,235 --> 00:52:51,938
Well. Alone at last.

958
00:52:51,938 --> 00:52:54,774
And with my sanity intact.

959
00:52:54,774 --> 00:52:57,711
You got eyes, come and fetch me.

960
00:52:58,378 --> 00:52:59,679
Or not quite.

961
00:52:59,679 --> 00:53:02,716
You got a mouth, please give me a call.

962
00:53:03,049 --> 00:53:05,218
A pair of drumsticks.

963
00:53:05,218 --> 00:53:07,787
An old sweater.

964
00:53:07,787 --> 00:53:09,956
A Diary of Joy.

965
00:53:09,956 --> 00:53:12,158
Are you trying to get rid of this?

966
00:53:12,158 --> 00:53:14,255
That bozo probably tried to steal it again.

967
00:53:15,128 --> 00:53:17,197
Everything gets taken away from me.

968
00:53:17,697 --> 00:53:19,599
Baggage only slows you down.

969
00:53:19,599 --> 00:53:21,501
The best travelers travel light.

970
00:53:21,501 --> 00:53:27,340
Of course, you could always get insurance.

971
00:53:27,034 --> 00:53:28,102
Property insurance!

972
00:53:28,408 --> 00:53:29,476
That’s a good idea.

973
00:53:29,476 --> 00:53:32,563
No, no, no.

974
00:53:33,346 --> 00:53:35,982
Spiritual insurance.

975
00:53:35,982 --> 00:53:37,851
Spiritual insurance.

976
00:53:37,851 --> 00:53:39,152
For your soul.

977
00:53:39,152 --> 00:53:40,887
My soul needs insuring?

978
00:53:40,887 --> 00:53:43,023
Somebody’s stealing my soul?

979
00:53:46,092 --> 00:53:49,396
We all misplace things along the way.

980
00:53:50,797 --> 00:53:53,566
Is it getting chilly in here?

981
00:53:53,566 --> 00:53:57,037
Suddenly, yes.

982
00:53:57,037 --> 00:53:59,005
Mercy, mercy.

983
00:54:01,675 --> 00:54:03,643
Better luck in the next life.

984
00:54:24,831 --> 00:54:34,074
The Master is more than just Kind.

985
00:54:34,708 --> 00:54:39,679
O friends, I could never have enough time

986
00:54:40,513 --> 00:54:51,291
To tell you of His boundless Grace.

987
00:54:53,059 --> 00:54:58,631
Only in the remote corner of my heart

988
00:54:58,631 --> 00:55:09,075
I humbly shed tears!

989
00:55:09,075 --> 00:55:12,679
When Thou appearest,

990
00:55:12,679 --> 00:55:16,716
The sun seems to fade!

991
00:55:16,716 --> 00:55:17,751
Thy being

992
00:55:17,751 --> 00:55:26,059
Shining as thousands of stars
and countless jewels,

993
00:55:26,086 --> 00:55:30,323
Thy holy and youthful glow

994
00:55:31,097 --> 00:55:43,076
Brighten the darkest corner of my soul.

995
00:55:43,076 --> 00:55:51,151
O my longing heart,

996
00:55:51,151 --> 00:55:55,422
Overfilled with joy!

997
00:55:55,422 --> 00:55:58,358
And divine gladness.

998
00:55:58,358 --> 00:56:02,896
While bathing in Thy infinite Splendor.

999
00:56:02,896 --> 00:56:04,464
All worldly burdens

1000
00:56:04,464 --> 00:56:06,466
and sorrows,

1001
00:56:06,466 --> 00:56:08,034
depart!

1002
00:56:08,034 --> 00:56:11,041
While bathing in Thy infinite Splendor.

1003
00:56:11,104 --> 00:56:16,242
All worldly burdens and sorrows,
depart!

1004
00:56:16,242 --> 00:56:20,447
There is none in this world

1005
00:56:20,447 --> 00:56:32,992
Who’s so full of Love and Mercy.

1006
00:56:33,426 --> 00:56:37,597
It would be my great honour

1007
00:56:37,597 --> 00:56:40,624
To be just a swallow,

1008
00:56:40,867 --> 00:56:45,005
Standing on one leg,

1009
00:56:45,005 --> 00:56:50,877
Life after life

1010
00:56:50,877 --> 00:57:09,062
Singing Her praise!

1011
00:57:50,603 --> 00:57:53,206
Who is there to praise?

1012
00:57:53,206 --> 00:57:57,277
Who? What? Nothing!

1013
00:57:57,444 --> 00:57:59,212
Money!

1014
00:57:59,212 --> 00:58:02,229
My father always said
praise money! And I do.

1015
00:58:03,817 --> 00:58:05,218
Where have you been?

1016
00:58:05,218 --> 00:58:06,653
Growing up.

1017
00:58:06,653 --> 00:58:10,156
The next car over.
It’s the world of wealth!

1018
00:58:10,156 --> 00:58:13,393
I learned all about big-time investing.

1019
00:58:13,393 --> 00:58:15,695
Do you need some financial advice?

1020
00:58:15,695 --> 00:58:18,031
Or a tax shelter?

1021
00:58:18,031 --> 00:58:20,166
You got to protect yourself for the future!

1022
00:58:20,166 --> 00:58:20,800
Invest right.

1023
00:58:20,008 --> 00:58:22,010
Learn to handle money.

1024
00:58:22,802 --> 00:58:25,705
Bozo, you keep your hands off my money.

1025
00:58:25,705 --> 00:58:26,506
Pete.

1026
00:58:26,506 --> 00:58:27,207
What?

1027
00:58:27,207 --> 00:58:28,641
The name’s Pete, lady.

1028
00:58:28,641 --> 00:58:31,478
Whatever. I don’t have time
for boys your age.

1029
00:58:31,478 --> 00:58:34,581
All right. Well,
I am making my father proud.

1030
00:58:34,581 --> 00:58:38,118
And nothing is going to get me off track.

1031
00:58:40,032 --> 00:58:41,800
Oh, wow.

1032
00:59:11,785 --> 00:59:14,587
O Lord,

1033
00:59:14,587 --> 00:59:17,824
You have numerous disciples.

1034
00:59:17,824 --> 00:59:19,926
I have only You!

1035
00:59:22,262 --> 00:59:24,531
Who is the most faithful of us two?

1036
00:59:24,531 --> 00:59:26,199
I pity myself openly!

1037
00:59:26,199 --> 00:59:28,301
I complain openly!

1038
00:59:28,301 --> 00:59:32,305
Does anyone hear me? (I do!)

1039
00:59:32,305 --> 00:59:35,372
My Master wouldn’t care the least

1040
00:59:35,975 --> 00:59:39,779
Master

1041
00:59:47,921 --> 00:59:54,127
Master, You must have forgotten to
use Your human eyes

1042
00:59:54,127 --> 00:59:59,532
Now that the heavenly one is
no longer shut.

1043
01:00:00,133 --> 01:00:07,040
That’s why You do not see me
in my lonely corner

1044
01:00:07,004 --> 01:00:11,575
Longing to see You.
(I’m longing to see you, too.)

1045
01:00:12,045 --> 01:00:17,017
You embrace the glory of the higher worlds,

1046
01:00:17,017 --> 01:00:19,986
It wouldn’t matter

1047
01:00:19,986 --> 01:00:25,990
If I am groveling alone in this dark domain!

1048
01:00:26,026 --> 01:00:29,123
O Ye the “perfect” Saint,

1049
01:00:29,996 --> 01:00:34,100
Why are Your eyes lost?

1050
01:00:41,975 --> 01:00:45,712
Master! Do You have ears at all?

1051
01:00:45,712 --> 01:00:46,646
You must!

1052
01:00:46,646 --> 01:00:50,750
In order to hear my desperate call.

1053
01:00:50,075 --> 01:00:51,310
I think...

1054
01:00:51,985 --> 01:00:56,723
I’ll buy a pair of human ears for You

1055
01:00:56,723 --> 01:00:59,526
Tomorrow.

1056
01:01:02,362 --> 01:01:09,376
I suspect that
You’ve lost Your heart somewhere

1057
01:01:09,969 --> 01:01:16,643
While ascending the heavenly abodes!

1058
01:01:17,777 --> 01:01:21,348
Or else You’d recognize my feeling

1059
01:01:21,348 --> 01:01:25,385
As my heart is forever hanging

1060
01:01:25,385 --> 01:01:26,986
On my sleeves,

1061
01:01:26,986 --> 01:01:33,560
Dying to make itself an offering

1062
01:01:33,056 --> 01:01:41,631
To You!

1063
01:01:42,135 --> 01:01:43,770
Dearest Master,

1064
01:01:43,077 --> 01:01:45,279
Please sympathize with

1065
01:01:45,972 --> 01:01:49,809
All my fellow beings
who are on the same boat,

1066
01:01:49,809 --> 01:01:53,813
Who long for Nirvana,

1067
01:01:53,813 --> 01:01:59,452
But all they know is samsara.

1068
01:01:59,953 --> 01:02:01,688
Dearest Master,

1069
01:02:01,688 --> 01:02:06,026
In the case that
You’ve lost the human heart,

1070
01:02:06,026 --> 01:02:13,867
Please take mine.

1071
01:02:15,135 --> 01:02:18,004
Please take mine.

1072
01:02:45,265 --> 01:02:46,833
Hey, lady, look what I landed!

1073
01:02:46,833 --> 01:02:51,237
Oh, Papa will be so proud.

1074
01:02:51,237 --> 01:02:53,773
Floozies, what next?

1075
01:02:53,773 --> 01:02:55,975
He’ll figure out how to juggle life.

1076
01:02:55,975 --> 01:02:57,610
I know already.

1077
01:02:57,061 --> 01:03:00,565
Oh, hey, watch this, baby!

1078
01:03:01,114 --> 01:03:03,550
Yes! Juggle knives!

1079
01:03:03,055 --> 01:03:05,757
Boys your age,
you think you’re immortal.

1080
01:03:06,252 --> 01:03:06,886
Men my age.

1081
01:03:06,886 --> 01:03:08,521
Start with oranges.

1082
01:03:10,069 --> 01:03:11,104
I could have done it.

1083
01:03:11,725 --> 01:03:13,993
Sure you could.

1084
01:03:13,993 --> 01:03:16,129
And what do you know about me?

1085
01:03:16,129 --> 01:03:20,000
I had a son.
You kids think you can do anything!

1086
01:03:20,000 --> 01:03:20,767
I can!

1087
01:03:20,767 --> 01:03:23,103
You take stupid risks!

1088
01:03:23,103 --> 01:03:25,238
And your family is left praying for you.

1089
01:03:25,238 --> 01:03:26,573
I’m going to be rich and famous!

1090
01:03:26,573 --> 01:03:28,308
And prayers go unanswered.

1091
01:03:28,308 --> 01:03:29,809
And the whole world will know my name!

1092
01:03:29,809 --> 01:03:30,877
And there is no God.

1093
01:03:30,877 --> 01:03:32,178
Or none worth forgiving.

1094
01:03:32,645 --> 01:03:35,048
And who needs God
when you have money?

1095
01:03:35,048 --> 01:03:37,150
And you end up alone
on a crowded street

1096
01:03:37,015 --> 01:03:39,384
looking for the face you won’t find.

1097
01:04:08,615 --> 01:04:11,051
The World is full of troubles

1098
01:04:11,051 --> 01:04:13,753
Only I’m so full of You!

1099
01:04:13,753 --> 01:04:18,024
If You were placed within the world

1100
01:04:18,892 --> 01:04:21,428
All the troubles would be removed.

1101
01:04:21,428 --> 01:04:24,164
But as the world is full of troubles,

